{
  "texts": [
    "Third, we clarify the AI-Act liability framework to apply to the three case studies in a comparative setting.",
    "For the comparative significance, concerning the focus of the AI-Act on risk-based AI, we directed the selection towards three categories of case studies (viz.",
    "highrisk, mid-risk and low-risk case studies).",
    "Even though the AI Act proposal/amendment distinguishes between high-risk and limited-risk AI, for practical research purposes, we have divided limited risk into mid-risk and low-risk to facilitate the creation of more detailed research findings and to show the practical difference between levels of limited risk and their impact.",
    "We do not discuss unacceptable AI or Generative AI in the methodology."
  ]
}